On Mon, 6 Dec 1999, Michael Bacarella wrote:
> Are there any living projects to add massive memory support to x86 Linux?
> Specifically, the Intel (36-bit) physical address space extensions.
check out the 'Processor type and features' configuration menu under the
'2.3.30' kernel, you'll find:
                      High Memory Support 
                            ( ) off
                            ( ) 4GB
                            (X) 64GB
we have full support for 64GB RAM.
-- mingo
